c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Airtable AI is best suited for operations teams, content teams, project managers, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Amie, meanwhile, shines for professionals, freelancers, calendar power users, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2012, Airtable AI describes itself as \"AI-enhanced flexible database platform for organizing any type of work.\" Amie, established in 2020, positions itself as \"Joyful calendar app combining scheduling, tasks, and availability sharing.\" With 8 years between them, Airtable AI brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Amie offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Airtable AI** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), more features (9 vs 6), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Amie is a poor choice — far from it. Amie excels in its own right, particularly for professionals and freelancers.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value most flexible database-spreadsheet hybrid, go with Airtable AI. If beautiful and joyful design matters more to you, Amie is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
